                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">C.F.M.</gloss> Files: Lot M–88: Box 2061: <gloss
                        target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Documents</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the <gloss type="from">French Delegation</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Council of Foreign Ministers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="16" xml:id="d228fn16">The substance of this proposal was presented by
                        Foreign Minister Bidault at the 32nd Meeting of the Council of Foreign
                        Ministers, July 2, and came under consideration by the Council at its 33rd
                        Meeting, July 3; see the United States Delegation Records of these meetings,
                            <ref target="#pg_715">pp. 715</ref> and <ref target="#pg_730">730</ref>,
                        respectively.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M.(46)</gloss> 181</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-02">2 July
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Peace Treaty With Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Statute of Trieste</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Trieste and the adjoining district shall form an autonomous territory
                    administered in accordance with a Statute proposed by the four Powers for
                    consideration by the Paris Conference and approval by the United Nations. The
                    United Nations Security Council shall ensure the integrity of the territory.</p>
            </div>
